{
  "texts": [
    "If the user's preferred algorithm performs slightly less well than the one at the top of the ranking, the user can decide to stick with his favorite algorithm.",
    "If you have enough time and hardware conditions, you can try more algorithms.",
    "Since we do not know how many algorithms a user might actually want to choose, consider providing a ranking of all the algorithms.",
    "In 1994, Brazdil, Gama and Henery first used metalearning algorithm recommendation to deal with sorting tasks (Brazdil, 1994).",
    "Later Nakhaeizadeh and Schnabl (1997), and later Keller et al. (2000), and Brazdil and Soares (2000) also adopted similar methods."
  ]
}